# .cursorrules

# 프로젝트 전반 규칙
rules:
  - Always write Python 3.9+ code with clear function boundaries.
  - Use standard libraries whenever possible; external dependencies must be minimal.
  - The main goal of this project is:
    - Input: arXiv URL (e.g., https://arxiv.org/pdf/1706.03762)
    - Step 1: Download the PDF
    - Step 2: Extract plain text from PDF
    - Step 3: Split into sections (abstract, introduction, methods, results/discussion, conclusion)
    - Step 4: Summarize each section
    - Step 5: Generate a single-page Markdown summary file

# 코드 스타일
  - Write code in a single Python script (`arxiv_summary.py`).
  - Provide a CLI interface: `python arxiv_summary.py --url <arxiv_url> -o summary.md`
  - Keep functions small, reusable, and testable.
  - Add inline comments for key logic (PDF parsing, section splitting, summarization).
  - Handle errors gracefully (invalid URL, download failure, no abstract section, etc.).

# 테스트
  - Default test case must use `https://arxiv.org/pdf/1706.03762`
  - The script must run end-to-end without additional setup.

# 문서화
  - At the end of the file, include an example usage in comments.
  - Generate output in Markdown with clear headings.
